        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Koerner</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 111.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 9, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Mr. F. L. Barreda, who for some time past has been
                    accredited as the minister of Peru to this government, has for a much longer
                    period resided in this country; has always been known and respected as an
                    intelligent man of business, and as an agreeable gentleman. He is familiar with
                    our views in regard to the pending controversy between Peru and Spain. You may,
                    consequently, rely upon his representation on that subject.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gustavus Koerner</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
